- "env_name" and "env_description" provide the name and description of each environment, respectively;
- "env_id" is a unique identifier for each environment;
- "DISTINCT" ensures that each combination of environment name, description, and ID is unique;
- "ORDER BY T1.env_name ASC" sorts the results alphabetically by the environment name.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT env_id, env_name, env_description
FROM environments
ORDER BY env_name ASC;

